+4. **Helper extensions:** `conformance/src/conformance/harness/_seed.py`
+   gets two minor adjustments:
 
+   - `submit_evaluate` is extended to include `metrics` in the wire
+     payload whenever explicitly passed by the caller (today it only
+     includes metrics when `status == "success"`). Required by the
+     eval_error-with-metrics test below: without this, the test would
+     silently send a metrics-less wire payload and the §4.4 "discard
+     submission-carried metrics" assertion would be trivially satisfied.
+     The helper change is shape-faithful: nothing else uses
+     `submit_evaluate` with non-success+metrics today, so the change
+     is additive. `submit_evaluate` also gets an `artifacts_uri: str |
+     None = None` parameter so the new artifacts_uri-not-equivalence
+     test (see Evaluator scenarios) can vary it without an inline POST.
+
+   - `submit_plan` is changed to always include `proposal_ids` in the
+     wire payload (it currently omits when `status="error"`), per the
+     §2.4 reading that `proposal_ids` is unconditionally part of the
+     submission shape. This is conforming under both literal-spec and
+     reference-impl readings (see Planner scenarios above).
+
